===Alternative forms===
* {{l|mul|⺼}} U+2EBC (when used as a component on the left side in composite characters)

The left component form {{lang|zh|sc=Hani|⺼}} appears very similar to {{lang|zh|sc=Hani|⺝}}, the left component form of {{m|mul|月||moon|sc=Hani}}, and is often drawn identically in compounds, although they are etymologically distinct. This is particularly an issue in looking up characters by radical; compare [[Appendix:Chinese radical/月|月 index]] and [[Appendix:Chinese radical/肉|肉 index]]. In Traditional Chinese, careful usage distinguishes the cross strokes, with ⺼ written with unattached diagonal strokes; in the historical Kangxi Dictionary, they appear identical.

The component form {{lang|zh|sc=Hani|⺼}} may also appear as {{zh-l|*𱼀}} in characters such as {{zh-l|*祭}}, {{zh-l|*然}}, and {{zh-l|*將}}. However, {{zh-l|*月}} may also take this form in rare cases such as {{zh-l|*望}}.

